# UX/UI System — how to work in it

## Before you edit UI — read these (mandatory)

For any change to `apps/web/**` or `packages/ui/**`, **before editing**:

1. `design-system/README.md` — the navigation map.
2. `design-system/principles.md` — tie-breaker order.
3. `design-system/ux-rules.md` — interaction & behavior rules.
4. `design-system/accessibility.md` — a11y baseline.
5. `design-system/responsive.md` — breakpoint behavior.

For specific work, also read:

- Tokens: `design-system/tokens/README.md` + the source
  `packages/ui/src/tokens/tokens.json`.
- New component: `design-system/components/README.md` (L1) or
  `design-system/patterns/README.md` (L2).
- Motion: `design-system/motion.md`.
- Copy: `design-system/content-guidelines.md`.

If those files don't yet exist in your context, **open them with the
file-read tool before proposing changes**. Do not infer the rules from
filenames.

## Tiers — pick the right home

| Tier | Lives in | Use when |
|------|----------|----------|
| **Tokens** | `packages/ui/src/tokens/tokens.json` | adding a new color/space/radius/motion value |
| **L1 Primitive** | `packages/ui/src/components/primitives/` | a new atomic UI element (button, input). **Requires DS-owner approval — stop and ask.** |
| **L2 Pattern** | `packages/ui/src/components/patterns/` | a composite reused across 2+ features |
| **L3 Feature** | `apps/web/src/components/<feature>/` | feature-specific one-off |

## Source of truth, by surface

| Surface | Where |
|---------|-------|
| Tokens (data) | `packages/ui/src/tokens/tokens.json` |
| Tokens (CSS vars, generated — do not edit) | `packages/ui/src/tokens/tokens.css` |
| Tokens (typed const, generated — do not edit) | `packages/ui/src/tokens/tokens.ts` |
| Tailwind theme | `packages/ui/tailwind.config.ts` (`apps/web` inherits via preset) |
| Lint enforcement | `packages/config/eslint/design-system.js` |
| AI rules (this file set) | `.cursor/rules/00..05-*.mdc` and `CLAUDE.md` |

## Decision flow before writing JSX

```
need a UI thing
  └─ does it exist in @famm/ui?           ── yes ──► import & use
        │ no
        └─ near-match in @famm/ui?         ── yes ──► extend its cva() variants
              │ no
              └─ reused across features?
                    ├─ yes ──► propose new L2 pattern
                    └─ no  ──► place as L3 in apps/web/src/components/<feature>/
```

If your need maps to "new L1 primitive", **stop and ask** before scaffolding.

## When uncertain

- Two valid patterns? Don't pick — ask.
- Token name doesn't fit? Don't invent a class string — propose the token
  in your reply.
- Rule conflicts with the request? Cite the rule and ask before bending it.

## After editing — explain your decisions

End every UI reply with a `Design-system decisions:` section listing:

1. Components reused (with paths).
2. Tokens chosen (and why if non-obvious).
3. A11y behavior preserved/added.
4. Anything flagged `OPEN:` for human review.

Skip this only for backend-only edits.
